data.text:
Nancy Ajram is a Lebanese singer who has been passionate about music ever since she was a kid. In 1998, she released her first album titled “Mehtagalak.” But the real turning point in her artistic career was in 2003 following the release of her album “Ya Salam.”

Ajram has released several successful albums throughout the course of her career including “Ya TabTab,” "Shakhbat Shakhabit", and “Befakar Fe Eh,” which won the World Music Award. Aside from singing, Ajram was a member of the jury of Arab Idol’s second and third season. Nancy Ajram has won several platinum awards, three World Music Awards. and three Murex d'Or Awards. She is also a UNICEF Goodwill Ambassador.
